        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[AI-assisted] fix(memory): close cached agent and state databases in test teardowns",
        "body": "��This PR resolves Windows file locking (EBUSY/EPERM) errors during test cleanup in the memory-core extension.\r\n\r\n### Cause\r\nWhen tests instantiate MemoryIndexManager using the default backend 'builtin', they register the agent database path which opens and caches the state database (openclaw.sqlite) connection via openOpenClawStateDatabase / registerAgentDatabase. The state database connection is cached globally in openclaw-state-db.ts's cachedDatabases and is never closed during the test's afterEach or afterAll hooks. On Windows, this open file handle locks the state database file, blocking the test suite from unlinking the temporary fixtureRoot directories.\r\n\r\n### Fix\r\nImport and invoke closeOpenClawAgentDatabasesForTest() and closeOpenClawStateDatabaseForTest() from 'openclaw/plugin-sdk/sqlite-runtime-testing' in afterEach and afterAll hooks of the affected memory-core test files to ensure all open SQLite database handles are fully closed before unlinking test directories.\r\n\r\nCloses #78640\r\n\r\nReal behavior proof: Ran vitest run extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.reindex-recovery.test.ts and vitest run extensions/memory-core/src/memory/manager.watcher-config.test.ts on a Windows host and confirmed all tests pass cleanly without EBUSY errors.\r\n\n\n## Windows Test Proof\nTests ran successfully via \\\node scripts/run-vitest.mjs\\ on Windows, exiting with 0. The EPERM/EBUSY errors are resolved because the database is properly closed before directory deletion in teardown.\r\n",
        "branch": "fix/memory-eperm-windows-copy",
